prefix: Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in biology would.
problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in biology would. Below is a drawing of all $26$ letters in the English alphabet. As drawn below, some of these letters could be portions of the graph of a function, and some cannot. For example, the $\textsf{O}$ resembles an ellipse, which cannot be part of the graph of a function.

As drawn below, which of these letters could be portions of the graph of a function? (You may not rotate them.)

Give your answer as a list of letters with no spaces or other punctuation between them, in alphabetic order.

$$\begin{array}{c c c c c}
\textsf{A} & \textsf{B} & \textsf{C} & \textsf{D} & \textsf{E}\\\\
\textsf{F} & \textsf{G} & \textsf{H} & \textsf{I} & \textsf{J}\\\\
\textsf{K} & \textsf{L} & \textsf{M} & \textsf{N} & \textsf{O}\\\\
\textsf{P} & \textsf{Q} & \textsf{R} & \textsf{S} & \textsf{T}\\\\
\textsf{U} & \textsf{V} & \textsf{W} & \textsf{X} & \textsf{Y}\\\\
&& \textsf{Z} &&
\end{array}$$
gpt_response:
The letters that could be portions of the graph of a function are those that pass the vertical line test. In other words, each vertical line intersects the graph of a function at most once.

Looking at the letters, we can see that the following letters could represent portions of the graph of a function: \textsf{F, G, I, J, K, L, S, T, U, V, W, X, Y, Z}. 

Therefore, the list of letters that could be portions of the graph of a function is: \textsf{FGIJKLSTUVWXYZ}.
